---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Najia Gul — I help AI teams create delightful products"
  description="Fractional product management for early-stage teams shipping AI products. I close the gap between what users want to achieve and how easily your product lets them — and build the evals to measure it."
>
  <!-- ============ hero ============ -->
  <section class="wrap hero">
    <span class="hand hello">hi, I'm Najia —</span>
    <h1>
      I help AI teams create
      <span class="squig">delightful<svg viewBox="0 0 300 24" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 14 C 40 4, 70 22, 105 12 S 175 4, 210 14 S 270 20, 296 10" /></svg></span>
      products.
    </h1>
    <p class="sub">
      A fractional product manager for early-stage teams shipping AI. I close the gap between
      what your users want to achieve and how easily your product lets them — and I build the
      evals that tell you whether each release shrank that gap.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="btn" href="mailto:najiagul.2000@gmail.com?subject=Working%20together">Email me</a>
      <a class="link-quiet" href="/blog/">Read the blog</a>
    </div>
    <span class="hand hand--teal note">that button opens my actual inbox — no funnel behind it</span>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ the gap ============ -->
  <section class="wrap reveal">
    <div class="card gap-card">
      <span class="hand label">the gap</span>
      <h2>Most AI products don't fail at the model.</h2>
      <p>
        They fail in the gap between what a user came to do and the work your product makes
        them do to get there. Demos hide that gap. Dashboards don't measure it. Users feel it
        inside five minutes — and they don't file a ticket, they leave.
      </p>
      <p>
        I've watched this from both sides: as a data scientist shipping models into enterprise
        products, and as a product manager deciding what ships at all. The teams that win
        aren't the ones with the best model. They're the ones who notice the gap first —
        because they measure it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ how I help ============ -->
  <section class="wrap work reveal" id="work">
    <span class="hand label">how I help</span>
    <h2>Fractional product management, built for AI teams</h2>
    <p class="lede">
      You get a PM a few days a week who has shipped inside fast-paced product organisations
      and doesn't need the AI part explained. Depending on where you are, that looks like:
    </p>

    <div class="offers">
      <div class="offer reveal">
        <h3>Find the gap</h3>
        <p>
          User interviews, session recordings, and your own usage data — turned into a ranked
          list of where users stall, give up, or route around your product. Not a 40-page
          report. A list your team can start on Monday.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="offer reveal">
        <h3>Ship like a product org</h3>
        <p>
          Clear specs, small releases, tight loops between product and engineering. I've
          worked inside enterprise product machines — I bring the cadence without the
          bureaucracy.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="offer offer--star reveal">
        <span class="hand star-note">where I'm most useful</span>
        <h3>Measure what you ship</h3>
        <p>
          Eval systems for your AI features: what "good" means for each one, written down and
          runnable. So when someone asks whether the new model actually made things better,
          the answer takes minutes — not a meeting.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ why me ============ -->
  <section class="wrap why reveal">
    <span class="hand label">why me</span>
    <h2>I've been the data scientist and the PM.</h2>
    <p>
      Before product, I was a data scientist and AI consultant at IBM, taking machine-learning
      systems from ambiguous business question to production for enterprise clients. Now I'm a
      product manager at SAP, where I build evaluation frameworks that help engineering teams
      ship faster — alongside a master's in data science and AI. I love telling stories backed
      by data.
    </p>
    <p>
      When your ML engineer and your designer disagree about what to build next, I'm useful in
      that room.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ final CTA ============ -->
  <section class="wrap reveal">
    <div class="card cta-card">
      <h2>Building an AI product, and shipping feels like guessing?</h2>
      <p>
        Tell me what you're building and where it hurts. If I can help, I'll say how. If I
        can't, I'll say that too.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="btn" href="mailto:najiagul.2000@gmail.com?subject=Working%20together">Email me</a>
        <span class="plain-email">or write to <a class="link-quiet" href="mailto:najiagul.2000@gmail.com">najiagul.2000@gmail.com</a></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  section { margin-top: 72px; }
  .hero { margin-top: 60px; padding-top: 28px; }

  .hello { font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5.2vw, 3.8rem);
    max-width: 16ch;
  }
  .sub {
    margin-top: 28px;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    max-width: 56ch;
    color: var(--body);
  }
  .cta-row {
    margin-top: 38px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 24px;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .note { font-size: 1.25rem; margin-top: 22px; }

  .label { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-bottom: 14px; }

  h2 { font-size: 1.85rem; max-width: 24ch; }
  section p { margin-top: 20px; max-width: 58ch; color: var(--body); }

  .gap-card { padding: 44px 46px; }

  .lede { margin-top: 20px; }
  .offers {
    margin-top: 36px;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 22px;
  }
  .offer {
    background: var(--card);
    border: 2px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 26px 26px 30px;
    box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 rgba(46, 42, 36, 0.15);
    position: relative;
  }
  .offer h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; }
  .offer p { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 0.97rem; }
  .offer--star { box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 var(--teal); }
  .star-note {
    position: absolute;
    top: -16px;
    right: 18px;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    background: var(--creme);
    padding: 0 8px;
  }

  .cta-card { padding: 44px 46px; }
  .plain-email { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .offers { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    section { margin-top: 56px; }
    .gap-card, .cta-card { padding: 32px 26px; }
  }
</style>
